<p>


I am a professor at EECS Department at 
<a href="http://www.berkeley.edu">UC Berkeley</a>, where I am part of 
the 
<a href="http://bair.berkeley.edu/">Berkeley Artificial Intelligence 
Research Lab (BAIR)</a>.  
Before that, I spent a decade on the 
faculty of the 
<a href="http://www.ri.cmu.edu/">Robotics Institute</a> at <a 
href="http://www.cmu.edu">CMU</a>.   I am also 
<a href="http://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~vgg/people.html">still remembered
</a> in <a 
href="https://flic.kr/s/aHskAiHGFr">lovely 
Oxford</a>, where I did a post-doc 
with <a href="http://www.robots.ox.ac.uk/~az">Andrew Zisserman</a>. 
During 2007-2015, I have also been closely collaborating with 
<a href="http://www.di.ens.fr/willow/">Team WILLOW</a>
at <a href="http://www.ens.fr/">&#201;cole Normale Sup&#233;rieure</a> / 
 <a href="http://www.inria.fr">INRIA</a>
in <a 
href="https://flic.kr/s/aHsju3GuLK"> 
beautiful Paris</a>.  Over the years, I was lucky to have some <a 
href="officemates.html">amazing 
officemates</a>.  
<p>



<h2>Research</h2>


The central goal of my research is to use vast amounts of unlabelled 
visual data to understand, model, and recreate the visual world around 
us.  My research has been mainly in data-driven computer vision, as well as its 
projection onto computer graphics and computational photography.  I have been working on  
autoregressive image generation <a 
href="research/NPS/efros-iccv99.pdf">since 
1999</a>, visual data scaling <a 
href="https://graphics.cs.cmu.edu/projects/scene-completion/">since 2007</a>,
self-supervised learning <a 
href="OUI2015.pdf">since 
2015</a>, continual learning 
<a href="https://slideslive.com/38930883/imagining-a-postdataset-era">since 2020</a>, and 
on what is now called "world models" <a 
href="https://pathak22.github.io/noreward-rl/">since 
2017</a>.  Other interests include human vision, visual 
data 
mining, 
robotics, and the applications of computer vision to the visual arts and 
the humanities.  I also enjoy making <a href="gelato_bet.html">scientific 
bets</a>.
<p>

For a high-level overview of my research, here are some of my
<a 
href="https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLJRtItMmpCFYUu_52nLs4BLLXriLk6Nhy&si=c6iNGUFeq6xCKq5g"> 
recent talks</a>.
Or, for something completely different, check out a (somewhat dated)
<a 
href="https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/11/12/in-the-age-of-ai-is-seeing-still-believing">New 
Yorker article</a> about some of our work.  Also, I was doing vision-based 
robotics <a 
href="https://aaai.org/ojs/index.php/aimagazine/article/download/1130/1048">before 
it was cool</a> (see picture on page 23 :). 
